    "macroSummary": "Trump's escalation threats against Iran are driving classic risk-off dynamics with oil spiking above $100 (stagflation threshold), dollar strengthening, and Bitcoin falling despite positive ETF flows. The geopolitical shock is overriding technical oversold conditions and threatening to shift the regime from relief rally back to risk-off deleveraging.",
    "regimeImpact": "Oil above $100 and dollar strength suggest the oversold relief rally is stalling, with potential regime shift to stagflationary bear market if Iran conflict escalates further.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Tighten BMNR cash-secured put strikes as Bitcoin risks breaking $62,300 structural support amid geopolitical pressure",
      "Prepare to add energy sector shorts if oil spike above $110 confirms stagflation regime that pressures growth names",
      "Monitor VIX above 25 regime line for confirmation that relief rally has ended and risk-off has resumed"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil prices jumping toward $110 breach the stagflation threshold and threaten economic growth assumptions.",
      "Bitcoin falling despite $1.32B ETF inflows suggests institutional demand can't offset macro headwinds.",
      "Dollar strength amid Iran conflict doubts indicates flight-to-quality overwhelming oversold technical conditions.",
      "Gold falling 4.2% despite geopolitical tensions shows dollar strength trumping safe-haven demand in current environment."
    ]
